    "css": "font-size: 25px; ",
    "text": "This room shows some examples of how CSS can be used to customize the appearance of dice. Like several other widget types, dice have theor own set of CSS values that can be changed. You can use the 'css' property to change overall aspects of the dice (but probably should just use 'faceCSS'. Use 'faceCSS' to set css parameters on all faces or on individual faces. And use the specific parameters 'pipColor', 'color', 'borderColor', and 'imageScale' to modify aspects specific to individual faces."
